The paper discusses the use of density functions in optimal control problems, which is a topic that falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The examples given in the paper are related to robot navigation (cs.RO) and traffic control (cs.CE), which further supports the likelihood of cs.SY and cs.RO as potential sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of Markov decision processes, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.CE are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
